<p>I am trying to test IPv6 on our custom board which supports Linux.  When I perform the following steps:</p>  <ol> <li><code>/sbin/ip -6 addr add 2001:0db8:0:f101::1/64 dev eth0</code></li> <li><code>ping6 -I eth0 2001:0db8:0:f101::1</code></li> </ol>  <p>On my Linux system, the ping succeeds.</p>  <p>When I try the same steps on the custom board, I get the following error message:</p>  <pre><code>**connect: Cannot assign requested address** </code></pre>